WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.825 --> 00:00:01.846
<v ->In the modern world,</v>

2
00:00:01.846 --> 00:00:03.786 line:15% 
people tend to see religion as an enemy,

3
00:00:03.786 --> 00:00:06.206 line:15% 
as a destructive force that keeps the masses

4
00:00:06.206 --> 00:00:08.825 line:15% 
kind of ignorant.

5
00:00:08.825 --> 00:00:10.709
I also had a totally negative view of religion

6
00:00:10.709 --> 00:00:12.788
until I started to explore Shamanism.

7
00:00:12.788 --> 00:00:15.949
To my surprise, I found that my trips with substances

8
00:00:15.949 --> 00:00:19.169
like ayahuasca, iboga and LSD actually seemed to

9
00:00:19.169 --> 00:00:21.608
confirm the validity of the mystical experience

10
00:00:21.608 --> 00:00:24.449
that religious texts have talked about through the ages.

11
00:00:24.449 --> 00:00:27.028
Tom Roberts argues that the revival of psychedelics

12
00:00:27.028 --> 00:00:29.328
is a second reformation.

13
00:00:29.328 --> 00:00:30.949
Before the first reformation,

14
00:00:30.949 --> 00:00:32.928
the Bible was only in Latin and only

15
00:00:32.928 --> 00:00:34.588
priests could read it.

16
00:00:34.588 --> 00:00:36.729
After Martin Luther, everyone could read the

17
00:00:36.729 --> 00:00:38.308
Word of God and they could learn about the visions

18
00:00:38.308 --> 00:00:40.168
of the prophets for themselves.

19
00:00:40.168 --> 00:00:42.949
When psychedelics became widely available in the 60s,

20
00:00:42.949 --> 00:00:45.069
many people were able to access the same kind of experiences

21
00:00:45.069 --> 00:00:47.968
that the prophets had had.

22
00:00:47.968 --> 00:00:49.789
They would have mystical visions,

23
00:00:49.789 --> 00:00:52.148
attain a sense of unity with the cosmos.

24
00:00:52.148 --> 00:00:53.669
They could even speak to spirits who would

25
00:00:53.669 --> 00:00:56.088
introduce themselves as gods or angels.

26
00:00:56.088 --> 00:00:57.949
So, the question is, could we evolve kind of

27
00:00:57.949 --> 00:01:00.028
a new religious structure that encompasses these

28
00:01:00.028 --> 00:01:02.589
new revelations, or can a new expression

29
00:01:02.589 --> 00:01:05.558
of the religious impulse emerge in our time?

30
